  "text": "Since the sum is weighted by edge-weights, \"heavy\" edges have a stronger impact and hence will be typically shorter. The first constraint (11) forces the nodes to be equally scattered along each of the axes. In this sense, the drawing has a perfectly balanced aspect ratio. The second constraint [CITATION_1] ensures that there is no correlation between the axes so that each additional dimension will provide us with as much new information as possible 1 .",
